Paleo-Accelerationist musings. 
No one wants Capitalism (the accelerationist 'real movement'). It's sheer Chernobyl, containment failure. 
Capitalism is what happens, despite everyone trying to stop it, due to auto-systematized social coordination failure. Competitive disunity, arms races, dynamic social disintegration is its space. 
China is an especially interesting case, because it is, over long-range history, the greatest containment operation  on earth. It was able to initiate the 'four great inventions of modernity' without letting modernity happen. It took the zero-ruptured fragmentation zone of the 15th century Mediterranean for paper, printing, gunpowder, and the compass to begin doing The Thing. 
What took China into acceleration was competitive international context. It became the preferred playground of Capital because the country was being left behind, and something had to be done about that. Once Western sclerosis took the pressure off, the return to techno-economic containment was to be expected. Quite probably, only China could have pulled this off. 
But now MAGA is ripping through the ramshackle containment structure that was built to inhibit American Capital over the long 20th century. International competition is going to be flooding back. Can China continue in its post Reform and Opening, runaway-reaction dampened mode under these circumstances? There might not even be time enough left for this to matter. ...
